WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.430
<b>Cape Promise</b>

21
00:02:06.860 --> 00:02:08.320
It's a flower!

22
00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:08.320
A flower?

23
00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.280
Oh, never mind. It's a person.

24
00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:16.570
What is he?

25
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:20.120
That old guy killed an imperial
squid in one fell swoop...

26
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:21.870
Was he just fishing...

27
00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:24.960
or was he trying to save us...?

28
00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:54.700
Say something already, jerk!

29
00:02:57.660 --> 00:03:00.200
I-If you wanna fight,
we'll fight, you bastard!

30
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:01.910
We've got cannons!

31
00:03:13.010 --> 00:03:15.880
You'd better stop what you're
doing before someone dies.

32
00:03:19.220 --> 00:03:20.510
Oh, yeah?

33
00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:21.760
And just who's gonna die?

34
00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:22.970
Me.

35
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:24.230
You?!

36
00:03:24.230 --> 00:03:25.020
You damn...

37
00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:26.060
Hey, calm down.

38
00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:28.480
That bastard's mocking us...

39
00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:31.770
Hey, gramps!

40
00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:34.650
How about you tell us
who you are and where we are.

41
00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.660
If you're going to ask a question,

42
00:03:46.330 --> 00:03:50.500
don't you think it's polite
to introduce yourself first?

43
00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:53.800
Huh? Oh, yeah, good point.

44
00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:54.960
Sorry about that.

45
00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:57.680
– My name is Crocus.
– I'm Roro... noa...

46
00:03:57.680 --> 00:04:00.890
I'm the lighthouse keeper
of the Twin Capes.

47
00:04:00.890 --> 00:04:02.720
I'm seventy-one and a Gemini.

48
00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:05.390
My blood type is AB.

49
00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.390
Let me cut him down!

50
00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:05.390
Hey, calm down.

51
00:04:05.390 --> 00:04:07.560
You want to know where we are?

52
00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:15.650
How dare you barge into my private
resort and run your mouth at me?

53
00:04:16.440 --> 00:04:19.990
Where do you think
we are? A rat's belly?

54
00:04:19.990 --> 00:04:22.830
S-So we were eaten
by the whale after all...

55
00:04:23.530 --> 00:04:26.200
But is this really the inside
of a whale's stomach?

56
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:29.120
Wait! What's gonna happen to us?!

57
00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:31.540
I don't wanna be digested!

58
00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:41.390
– Cut that out already!
– Cut that out already!

59
00:04:41.390 --> 00:04:44.100
Haven't you kids heard
of the running gag?

60
00:04:44.100 --> 00:04:44.970
– That was a gag?!
– That was a gag?!

61
00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:46.970
The exit is over there.

62
00:04:46.970 --> 00:04:48.480
– We can get out?!
– We can get out?!

63
00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:52.900
Hold on a sec! Why is there
an exit in a whale's stomach?!

64
00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:55.190
And why is the door in the sky?!

65
00:04:55.190 --> 00:04:57.900
Wait... Look at it carefully...

66
00:04:57.900 --> 00:05:02.160
This sky... Those seagulls...

67
00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:04.080
They're all painted!

68
00:05:04.080 --> 00:05:06.450
It's all a painting inside
the whale's stomach!

69
00:05:06.450 --> 00:05:07.660
Huh?!

70
00:05:07.660 --> 00:05:09.290
Call it a doctor's whimsy.

71
00:05:09.290 --> 00:05:11.670
What the hell are you
doing in here, you bastard?!

72
00:05:11.670 --> 00:05:13.380
That's enough. Just ignore him.

73
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:14.460
Agreed.

74
00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:17.000
Nami! We found the exit,
so let's just get out of here.

75
00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:18.420
Yeah.

76
00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:24.510
What's going on?!

77
00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:27.220
It's started again...

78
00:05:28.350 --> 00:05:29.230
Look at that!

79
00:05:30.020 --> 00:05:31.350
That's not an island!

80
00:05:31.350 --> 00:05:33.650
It's a ship! One that's made of iron!

81
00:05:33.650 --> 00:05:37.150
Oh, of course! It's because
this sea is gastric acid!

82
00:05:37.150 --> 00:05:40.820
Then our wooden ship's gonna
dissolve if we stay here too long.

83
00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:43.030
Hey! What's started?!

84
00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:45.030
Tell us!

85
00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:47.200
It's this whale...

86
00:05:48.700 --> 00:05:53.170
Laboon has started ramming
his head into the Red Line.

87
00:06:02.590 --> 00:06:03.510
– What?!
– What?!

88
00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:07.510
Come to think of it, the whale
had terrible scars on his forehead.

89
00:06:07.510 --> 00:06:09.640
And the way he howled at the sky...

90
00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:11.230
So what?

91
00:06:12.100 --> 00:06:13.690
He's suffering!

92
00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:24.110
Oh, so that's what
the geezer's doing here!

93
00:06:24.110 --> 00:06:25.030
Most likely.

94
00:06:25.030 --> 00:06:28.080
He's probably trying to kill
the whale from the inside!

95
00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:28.910
Now...

96
00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:31.160
What a vicious way to kill it!

97
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:33.540
Alright, mystery solved.
Now let's go, quick.

98
00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:35.370
We'll be digested if we stay too long.

99
00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:39.380
We have nothing to say
about his whale hunting,

100
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:41.590
nor do we have any reason
to save the whale.

101
00:06:41.590 --> 00:06:42.880
Let's get out of here.

102
00:06:57.060 --> 00:07:00.520
Dammit! With the waves
surging like this,

103
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:02.650
I don't know if we can
even reach the doors!

104
00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:04.950
We're gonna have
to paddle! Grab the oars!

105
00:07:04.950 --> 00:07:07.910
Let's speed it up!
I'm worried about Luffy.

106
00:07:07.910 --> 00:07:09.280
He's outside!

107
00:07:09.280 --> 00:07:11.240
I saw him fly out of the mouth!

108
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.000
The old man dove in!

109
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:16.790
Huh?

110
00:07:17.290 --> 00:07:19.790
What's he doing?
He's gonna be dissolved.

111
00:07:30.180 --> 00:07:32.560
What?! What's going on?!
Huh? Why?!

112
00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:33.810
Dizzy... Dizzy...

113
00:07:33.810 --> 00:07:36.190
I'm getting dizzy!

114
00:07:44.190 --> 00:07:45.440
What now?

115
00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:48.240
Is this the sea? A river? A canal?

116
00:07:58.290 --> 00:08:02.170
Okay. We've infiltrated
this far successfully.

117
00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:04.630
<b>Miss Wednesday
Mysterious Woman</b>

118
00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:04.630
Listen, Miss Wednesday.

119
00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:06.880
The stomach is right
behind these doors,

120
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:09.510
and that geezer is
most likely there too.

121
00:08:09.510 --> 00:08:12.140
We must eliminate him.

122
00:08:12.180 --> 00:08:15.020
<b>Mr. 9
Mysterious Man</b>

123
00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:15.020
Our goal is the whale.

124
00:08:15.390 --> 00:08:17.020
That's right, Mr. 9.

125
00:08:17.020 --> 00:08:21.480
This whale will be precious,
sweet honey to our town.

126
00:08:24.230 --> 00:08:26.320
Hey! The geezer came back up!

127
00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:27.320
Forget about him.

128
00:08:27.320 --> 00:08:30.820
More importantly, how are
we gonna open those doors?

129
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:33.830
Okay, Miss Wednesday,

130
00:08:33.830 --> 00:08:36.330
we'll open them on
"Three, two, one, baby!"

131
00:08:36.330 --> 00:08:37.460
Be on your guard.

132
00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:40.420
Roger, Mr. 9.
I'm ready when you are.

133
00:08:42.920 --> 00:08:48.090
I can't stop!

134
00:08:44.050 --> 00:08:45.710
What is this voice, Mr. 9?

135
00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:48.090
I don't know, Miss Wednesday.

136
00:08:58.310 --> 00:08:59.440
Not them again...!

137
00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:03.770
This is bad, Miss Wednesday!

138
00:09:03.770 --> 00:09:06.320
There's a sea of gastric acid below us!

139
00:09:07.900 --> 00:09:08.740
Luffy?

140
00:09:08.740 --> 00:09:11.320
Hey! So everyone's okay?

141
00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:14.740
Anyway... help me!

142
00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:23.000
Two more weirdos
came down with Luffy...

143
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:25.170
Hey! That old man disappeared!

144
00:09:25.170 --> 00:09:28.210
Forget him. We gotta save Luffy!

145
00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:44.940
Stop it, Laboon.

146
00:09:45.520 --> 00:09:48.530
Don't hurt yourself any more.

147
00:09:48.530 --> 00:09:50.990
There isn't much sedative left...

148
00:09:50.990 --> 00:09:53.450
I'll have to make some more.

149
00:09:55.950 --> 00:09:59.540
That wall divides the world's oceans.

150
00:09:59.540 --> 00:10:04.540
It won't break, even if you hit it
until you die, Laboon.

151
00:10:09.460 --> 00:10:10.840
It's calmed down!

152
00:10:10.840 --> 00:10:12.590
The whale is quiet now.

153
00:10:12.590 --> 00:10:14.470
Seems like it.

154
00:10:14.970 --> 00:10:16.100
Now...

155
00:10:17.010 --> 00:10:20.560
We ended up saving you guys
too, but who are you?

156
00:10:21.390 --> 00:10:24.350
Mr. 9, these people are pirates.

157
00:10:24.350 --> 00:10:26.520
I-I know, Miss Wednesday.

158
00:10:27.230 --> 00:10:32.030
B-But if we explain it to them,
they should understand... perhaps...

159
00:10:32.030 --> 00:10:34.490
You thugs are still at it?

160
00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:37.410
How many times do
I need to tell you?!

161
00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:42.580
You'll never lay a finger on
Laboon as long as I live!

162
00:10:45.170 --> 00:10:46.380
He's back.

163
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.040
Who's that old guy?

164
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:52.920
No matter what you say,
we can't just leave.

165
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:55.630
Our mission is to
take down this whale.

166
00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:58.510
You won't interfere with
our whale hunting this time!

167
00:10:58.510 --> 00:11:01.560
We'll blast a hole in his stomach!

168
00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:03.310
Let's go, baby!

169
00:11:02.350 --> 00:11:03.310
Roger!

170
00:11:09.020 --> 00:11:11.150
Those bastards!

171
00:11:15.490 --> 00:11:17.660
The old guy jumped
right into the shots!

172
00:11:17.660 --> 00:11:20.160
Was he... protecting the whale?!

173
00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:25.120
Stop this futile resistance!

174
00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:27.290
Protect this whale all you want!

175
00:11:27.830 --> 00:11:31.050
But this whale will become
food for our town!

176
00:11:37.180 --> 00:11:38.430
What's going on?

177
00:11:46.390 --> 00:11:47.900
They just...

178
00:11:47.900 --> 00:11:49.150
had it coming.

179
00:11:54.070 --> 00:11:57.820
I thank you for saving me... but why?

180
00:11:57.820 --> 00:11:59.410
I wasn't trying to save you.

181
00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:01.700
I just didn't like them.

182
00:12:02.740 --> 00:12:05.660
Hey, Luffy! What're you doing?
So, who are these guys?

183
00:12:05.660 --> 00:12:08.580
And what are you doing
inside this whale?

184
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.580
Stop it!

185
00:12:08.580 --> 00:12:12.000
Hey! Hey, Luffy! Stop it!
They're thugs from a nearby town.

186
00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:14.800
They're after whale meat.

187
00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:14.260
What are you trying to do?

188
00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:16.010
It belongs to someone else.

189
00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:17.130
If they capture Laboon,

190
00:12:17.130 --> 00:12:20.760
they'd be able to feed their town
for at least two to three years.

191
00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:22.050
Laboon?

192
00:12:22.050 --> 00:12:24.140
That's the name of this whale.

193
00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:29.480
He's an island whale, a species
that only lives in the West Blue.

194
00:12:29.480 --> 00:12:32.230
They're the biggest
whales in the world.

195
00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:35.360
I won't let them use him as food.

196
00:12:35.780 --> 00:12:39.110
There's a reason he keeps hitting
himself against the Red Line

197
00:12:39.110 --> 00:12:44.330
and howling toward Reverse Mountain.

198
00:12:44.330 --> 00:12:45.080
A reason?

199
00:12:45.080 --> 00:12:46.290
Yes.

200
00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:52.210
He's a whale with a human heart.

201
00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:57.630
And he's been devotedly waiting
for a certain pirate crew...

202
00:13:01.300 --> 00:13:03.510
for fifty long years...

203
00:13:03.970 --> 00:13:08.480
This... is Laboon's story...

204
00:13:21.990 --> 00:13:26.660
One day, while I was on duty
as the lighthouse keeper,

205
00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:31.040
some good-natured pirates
came down Reverse Mountain

206
00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:33.710
to enter the Grand Line.

207
00:13:33.710 --> 00:13:38.340
And a small whale came down too,
seemingly following them.

208
00:13:38.340 --> 00:13:40.920
That was Laboon.

209
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:45.970
As I said before, the island whale
is the largest whale species,

210
00:13:45.970 --> 00:13:47.640
and only lives in the West Blue.

211
00:13:48.640 --> 00:13:52.640
The pirates had been traveling
with Laboon the entire time,

212
00:13:52.640 --> 00:13:59.360
but they left him behind because of
how dangerous the Grand Line is.

213
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:01.780
But Laboon followed
without them noticing.

214
00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:07.830
Island whales usually travel
with their families in pods,

215
00:14:08.370 --> 00:14:13.290
but I suppose Laboon felt
that the pirates were his family.

216
00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:18.630
Since their ship had broken down,
they stayed here for several months.

217
00:14:18.630 --> 00:14:22.380
We became close friends in that time.

218
00:14:24.010 --> 00:14:26.970
Because of that, on the day
of their departure...

219
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:29.600
I need to ask you a favor, my friend.

220
00:14:29.600 --> 00:14:32.230
Can you take care of Laboon
for two or three years?

221
00:14:32.770 --> 00:14:36.310
We'll return after sailing
around the world.

222
00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:40.110
Listen up, Laboon.

223
00:14:40.110 --> 00:14:43.700
We're going to enter the Grand Line
and circumnavigate the world.

224
00:14:43.700 --> 00:14:46.120
But please wait for us here.

225
00:14:46.450 --> 00:14:48.370
We're going to a dangerous place.

226
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:50.700
Too dangerous for you to come along.

227
00:14:51.330 --> 00:14:54.160
Don't worry. Three years
will go by in a flash.

228
00:14:54.160 --> 00:14:55.420
Don't forget...

229
00:14:55.920 --> 00:14:58.670
We'll always be family,
no matter how far apart we are.

230
00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:04.630
Well then, we're setting off.

231
00:15:08.390 --> 00:15:10.470
Guys! We're setting sail!

232
00:15:10.470 --> 00:15:12.020
Hoist the anchor!

233
00:15:12.020 --> 00:15:13.480
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

234
00:15:17.690 --> 00:15:18.940
Laboon!

235
00:15:20.150 --> 00:15:22.230
Wait for us, Laboon!

236
00:15:22.230 --> 00:15:24.700
We promise to return!

237
00:15:24.700 --> 00:15:26.320
Mark my words!

238
00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:41.800
But that was fifty long years ago...

239
00:15:41.800 --> 00:15:43.050
Fifty years?

240
00:15:43.050 --> 00:15:46.430
Laboon's been waiting for those
guys for fifty whole years?

241
00:15:46.430 --> 00:15:50.470
Is that why he continues
to howl and ram into the rocks?

242
00:15:50.470 --> 00:15:51.260
Correct.

243
00:16:00.690 --> 00:16:02.440
This is an amazing canal.

244
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:05.490
I'm surprised that he's alive
with a hole like this in him.

245
00:16:05.490 --> 00:16:07.110
Was this also your old "whimsy"?

246
00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:08.950
A "doctor's whimsy."

247
00:16:08.950 --> 00:16:09.820
Doctor?

248
00:16:09.820 --> 00:16:12.080
I may not look it,
but yes, I'm a doctor.

249
00:16:12.080 --> 00:16:15.330
I used to run a clinic on
the cape many years ago.

250
00:16:15.330 --> 00:16:17.960
I was also a ship's
doctor for a few years.

251
00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:19.170
Really?

252
00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:21.750
You should be one for our ship!

253
00:16:21.750 --> 00:16:23.550
Don't be ridiculous.

254
00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:27.720
I no longer have the energy to keep
up with you reckless youngsters.

255
00:16:27.720 --> 00:16:31.010
A doctor, huh? That explains why
the whale's insides are like this...

256
00:16:31.010 --> 00:16:32.720
So this is from the treatment?

257
00:16:33.180 --> 00:16:34.720
That's right.

258
00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:40.400
It's impossible to treat a whale
this big from the outside.

259
00:16:41.150 --> 00:16:42.520
I'm opening the doors.

260
00:16:53.450 --> 00:16:55.200
There it is!

261
00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.620
The real sky!

262
00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:08.300
Miss Wednesday, what are you...

263
00:17:10.550 --> 00:17:12.720
A whole fifty years, huh?

264
00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:15.180
Those pirates sure are
making him wait...

265
00:17:15.180 --> 00:17:16.430
Idiot.

266
00:17:16.430 --> 00:17:18.520
This is the Grand Line.

267
00:17:18.850 --> 00:17:20.270
They're dead.

268
00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:23.610
They won't come back
no matter how long he waits.

269
00:17:23.610 --> 00:17:26.320
Why are you being so cynical?!

270
00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:28.610
You don't know that for sure!

271
00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:30.450
They could still come back!

272
00:17:30.450 --> 00:17:32.360
It's such a touching story!

273
00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:35.580
A whale believing in his friends'
promise for fifty long years...

274
00:17:35.580 --> 00:17:37.700
Isn't it, pops?!

275
00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:39.040
Yeah...

276
00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:42.290
But unfortunately, reality is cruel.

277
00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:46.920
I heard from a reliable source...

278
00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:50.010
that they fled the Grand Line.

279
00:17:50.010 --> 00:17:51.550
No way...

280
00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:54.470
You're telling me
they left him behind?!

281
00:17:55.720 --> 00:17:57.810
Fled the Grand Line...

282
00:17:57.810 --> 00:18:00.180
So they crossed
the Calm Belt and lived?

283
00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:02.640
Whether they're alive or not,

284
00:18:02.640 --> 00:18:05.110
I doubt they'll ever return.

285
00:18:05.110 --> 00:18:08.320
Seasons. Weather.
Current. Wind direction.

286
00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:10.570
They're all random here.

287
00:18:10.570 --> 00:18:13.950
Common sense is useless
in the Grand Line.

288
00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:18.790
Weak hearts soon succumb
to fear on the Grand Line.

289
00:18:18.790 --> 00:18:22.410
So the weak of heart
chose to run away,

290
00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:26.290
caring more about their lives
than the promise they made...

291
00:18:28.090 --> 00:18:30.840
They abandoned the whale?!

292
00:18:30.840 --> 00:18:33.470
While he's been waiting
here for fifty years?!

293
00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:34.680
That's too cruel!

294
00:18:35.220 --> 00:18:38.470
If you know that,
why haven't you told him?

295
00:18:38.810 --> 00:18:41.600
He can understand
human speech, right?

296
00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:43.270
I did tell him.

297
00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:45.730
I tried to tell him the whole story.

298
00:18:46.310 --> 00:18:48.520
Laboon! Listen up!

299
00:18:48.520 --> 00:18:51.570
I heard that those pirates
have fled the Grand Line.

300
00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:54.450
I know that you were friends,

301
00:18:54.780 --> 00:18:58.450
and that the promise they made
with you was certainly genuine...

302
00:19:04.540 --> 00:19:06.330
But I'm afraid...

303
00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:08.840
they will never return...

304
00:19:29.110 --> 00:19:31.780
Laboon! Listen to me!

305
00:19:31.780 --> 00:19:33.490
They will never–

306
00:19:42.580 --> 00:19:45.250
I understand that you
don't want to believe it...

307
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:49.380
but you must accept it somehow!

308
00:19:50.040 --> 00:19:50.750
Laboon!

309
00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:56.840
Laboon!

310
00:20:07.100 --> 00:20:12.940
It was on that day that he began
howling at Reverse Mountain

311
00:20:12.940 --> 00:20:16.570
and ramming his body
against the Red Line...

312
00:20:16.570 --> 00:20:18.490
It's as if he's insisting

313
00:20:18.490 --> 00:20:23.240
they will come down the other side
of that wall any day now...

314
00:20:23.830 --> 00:20:25.120
What a whale...

315
00:20:25.120 --> 00:20:27.290
Even though there's
no point in waiting...

316
00:20:27.290 --> 00:20:31.250
He refuses to believe me because if
I'm right, there would be no reason to wait.

317
00:20:31.920 --> 00:20:35.920
He's afraid of that
more than anything.

318
00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:38.220
His home is in the West Blue...

319
00:20:38.630 --> 00:20:40.590
but there's no way
to return from here.

320
00:20:40.590 --> 00:20:46.730
Those pirates were not only his friends,
but his hope for going home.

321
00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:50.730
While I do feel bad for the whale,

322
00:20:50.730 --> 00:20:53.520
they betrayed you, too, right?

323
00:20:55.860 --> 00:20:58.450
Haven't you taken care
of him long enough?

324
00:20:58.450 --> 00:21:01.110
Look at the scars on his forehead!

325
00:21:01.110 --> 00:21:06.540
If he continues to ram his head
like that, he'll surely die.

326
00:21:06.540 --> 00:21:09.870
It's an odd relationship, but I've
been with him for fifty years.

327
00:21:09.870 --> 00:21:11.920
I can't just stand by
and watch him die.

328
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:16.380
What's that idiot doing now?

329
00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:18.130
We only looked away for a second...

330
00:21:18.130 --> 00:21:20.090
Does he think he's
a mountain climber?

331
00:21:21.890 --> 00:21:24.510
Gum-Gum...

332
00:21:24.510 --> 00:21:26.600
Bouquet!

333
00:21:26.930 --> 00:21:28.730
Isn't that a mast?

334
00:21:28.730 --> 00:21:30.730
Yep. The one from our ship.

335
00:21:30.730 --> 00:21:32.020
The main mast, yes.

336
00:21:32.350 --> 00:21:34.650
Hey! Don't break the ship!

337
00:21:41.450 --> 00:21:43.910
– What the hell are you doing?!
– What the hell are you doing?!

338
00:21:54.710 --> 00:21:55.790
Wha...?! Hey, kid!

339
00:21:56.170 --> 00:21:59.210
Don't worry! He can't die
from being crushed!

340
00:22:04.010 --> 00:22:04.850
Dummy!

341
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:13.020
What's he thinking?

342
00:22:17.070 --> 00:22:20.240
Luffy! What the hell
are you trying to do?!

343
00:22:25.070 --> 00:22:26.200
It's a draw!

344
00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:32.290
I'm pretty strong, huh?

345
00:22:34.370 --> 00:22:36.790
Our fight isn't over yet!

346
00:22:36.790 --> 00:22:38.800
We'll have to settle things later!

347
00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:42.380
Your friends might be dead,
but I'll always be your rival!

348
00:22:42.380 --> 00:22:46.600
One day, we definitely gotta
settle this and see who's stronger.

349
00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:50.390
After we go around the Grand Line,
we'll come back to see you again.

350
00:22:51.730 --> 00:22:53.690
When I come back,
we'll finish our fight!

351
00:23:09.280 --> 00:23:10.450
Perfect.

352
00:23:10.450 --> 00:23:14.330
This symbol means
we promise to fight again.

353
00:23:14.330 --> 00:23:20.340
So don't ram into stuff or you'll
erase it before we get back. Got it?!

354
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:25.510
Alright!

355
00:23:27.390 --> 00:23:28.510
Where'd those guys go?

356
00:23:28.510 --> 00:23:29.970
"Those guys"?

357
00:23:29.970 --> 00:23:31.850
Oh, you mean those two weirdos?

358
00:23:31.850 --> 00:23:33.350
Maybe they ran away?

359
00:23:33.350 --> 00:23:36.650
We never did find out
what their deal was, huh...

360
00:23:39.560 --> 00:23:42.860
Whatever do we do now,
Miss Wednesday?

361
00:23:45.150 --> 00:23:48.910
At the very least, we'll need to
go back and report to the boss...

362
00:23:48.910 --> 00:23:51.660
We were supposed to finish
this mission long ago.

363
00:23:51.660 --> 00:23:55.620
You're right. It would be bad if they
begin to suspect us of treachery.

364
00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:56.750
Indeed.

365
00:23:56.750 --> 00:24:00.090
Since we lost our weapons, we have
to return to base and start over.

366
00:24:00.090 --> 00:24:04.210
If we must. Well then,
let us... begin... Huh?

367
00:24:04.210 --> 00:24:06.550
Um...? Where is...? What?!

368
00:24:06.880 --> 00:24:07.880
What's the matter?

369
00:24:09.430 --> 00:24:10.140
It's gone...

370
00:24:10.140 --> 00:24:10.760
What?

371
00:24:13.520 --> 00:24:14.430
What's this?

372
00:24:15.180 --> 00:24:17.230
You dropped the log pose?!

373
00:24:17.230 --> 00:24:18.940
I apologize, Miss Wednesday!

374
00:24:18.940 --> 00:24:21.230
And we need it to return home...

375
00:24:23.230 --> 00:24:24.360
As it stands–

376
00:24:25.860 --> 00:24:28.240
I-Is that...?!

377
00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:28.950
Huh?

378
00:24:30.530 --> 00:24:31.780
It's...

379
00:24:32.740 --> 00:24:34.700
O-Oh no...

380
00:24:35.620 --> 00:24:36.910
...the Unluckies!

381
00:24:36.910 --> 00:24:38.210
Darn! Are we too late?!

382
00:24:37.330 --> 00:24:41.130
<b>Miss Friday

Mysterious
Vulture Mr. 13

Mysterious
Sea Otter</b>

383
00:24:38.210 --> 00:24:39.290
Mr. 13!

384
00:24:39.290 --> 00:24:41.130
Miss Friday!

385
00:24:41.460 --> 00:24:43.800
Please wait! We can explain!

386
00:24:43.800 --> 00:24:46.510
We'll report to the boss immediately!

387
00:25:00.650 --> 00:25:04.980
Now then! I finally get to
chart out our Grand Line journey.

388
00:25:09.780 --> 00:25:13.660
Alright! I can finally cook up
the elephant bluefin tuna!

389
00:25:13.660 --> 00:25:15.160
Damn...!

390
00:25:16.120 --> 00:25:20.120
What was Luffy thinking,
wrecking our ship! Really...

391
00:25:20.120 --> 00:25:21.420
Hey, Zoro!

392
00:25:21.420 --> 00:25:24.210
Give me a hand!
I'm not exactly a shipwright!

393
00:25:30.130 --> 00:25:31.720
What's with the screaming?

394
00:25:31.720 --> 00:25:33.600
Is all well, Nami?!

395
00:25:33.600 --> 00:25:35.760
If you're hungry, I have
our meal right here!

396
00:25:35.760 --> 00:25:36.560
Time to eat?

397
00:25:36.890 --> 00:25:39.020
Th-The compass is broken!

398
00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:41.230
It's not pointing anywhere!

399
00:25:41.230 --> 00:25:42.900
Hey, you're right.

400
00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:45.020
It keeps spinning.

401
00:25:45.020 --> 00:25:46.690
Whoa! Neat!

402
00:25:47.570 --> 00:25:51.490
Looks like you guys
came here unprepared.

403
00:25:51.490 --> 00:25:54.570
For heaven's sake!
Did you come here to die?

404
00:25:55.030 --> 00:25:55.660
What?

405
00:25:55.660 --> 00:25:56.370
Food?

406
00:25:56.370 --> 00:25:58.200
You'll be eating hay.

407
00:25:58.200 --> 00:25:59.660
I thought I told you...

408
00:25:59.660 --> 00:26:03.080
Common sense is useless in this sea.

409
00:26:03.080 --> 00:26:06.380
It's not that the compass is broken...

410
00:26:07.170 --> 00:26:09.380
Then, is it the magnetic fields?

411
00:26:09.380 --> 00:26:10.470
Correct.

412
00:26:10.470 --> 00:26:15.850
The islands in the Grand Line
are rich in magnetic minerals.

413
00:26:15.850 --> 00:26:18.600
They cause abnormalities
throughout the Grand Line.

414
00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:22.020
Furthermore, the current and wind
patterns are never consistent.

415
00:26:22.020 --> 00:26:25.860
As a navigator, you should know
how terrifying that is.

416
00:26:25.860 --> 00:26:30.070
We'll have no hope of survival without
a way to know our direction...

417
00:26:30.070 --> 00:26:31.030
Yummy!

418
00:26:31.030 --> 00:26:33.150
I-I didn't know! Oh, well...

419
00:26:33.150 --> 00:26:35.780
Hey! That's really bad!
Are we gonna be okay?!

420
00:26:35.780 --> 00:26:38.240
This isn't bad. It's yummy!

421
00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:41.200
Can you guys be quiet
for one second?!

422
00:26:41.200 --> 00:26:44.370
The nose of the elephant
bluefin tuna tastes good!

423
00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:49.840
You need a log pose to travel
around the Grand Line.

424
00:26:49.840 --> 00:26:52.090
Log pose? I've never heard of it.

425
00:26:52.090 --> 00:26:56.090
It's a special compass
that can record magnetism.

426
00:26:56.090 --> 00:26:57.640
Like a weird-looking compass?

427
00:26:57.640 --> 00:27:00.220
Yes, its shape is quite unusual.

428
00:27:00.220 --> 00:27:01.640
Something like this?

429
00:27:01.640 --> 00:27:02.770
Yeah, that's the one.

430
00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:08.150
It's impossible to navigate
the Grand Line without a log pose.

431
00:27:08.900 --> 00:27:10.400
I see.

432
00:27:10.400 --> 00:27:12.150
But hold on a second...

433
00:27:12.650 --> 00:27:14.070
Luffy?

434
00:27:14.450 --> 00:27:17.070
How come you have one?!

435
00:27:18.780 --> 00:27:22.870
Those two weirdos
dropped it on the ship.

436
00:27:22.870 --> 00:27:24.040
They did?

437
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:25.420
Why'd you hit me?

438
00:27:25.420 --> 00:27:26.370
It felt right.

439
00:27:26.370 --> 00:27:27.330
Fair enough.

440
00:27:28.590 --> 00:27:29.920
So this is a log pose.

441
00:27:29.920 --> 00:27:31.460
There's no dial face.

442
00:27:31.460 --> 00:27:39.050
The magnetic fields of islands in
the Grand Line follow a certain rule:

443
00:27:39.050 --> 00:27:44.230
By recording the magnetism of
two islands pulling against each other,

444
00:27:44.230 --> 00:27:46.730
you can find the route
to the next island.

445
00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:50.400
Since you can't even figure out
your location in this sea,

446
00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:54.240
the magnetic record of the log pose
is the only thing you can depend on.

447
00:27:54.690 --> 00:28:01.370
To begin, you must pick one of
Reverse Mountain's seven magnetic fields.

448
00:28:01.370 --> 00:28:04.290
But no matter which route you take,

449
00:28:04.290 --> 00:28:08.170
the magnetic pulls will eventually
push you onto one route.

450
00:28:08.170 --> 00:28:11.710
And the name of the island
at the end of the voyage is...

451
00:28:12.210 --> 00:28:13.550
Laugh Tale.

452
00:28:13.550 --> 00:28:16.340
It's the last island in the Grand Line.

453
00:28:16.340 --> 00:28:20.550
The only one in history to confirm
its existence is the King of the Pirates.

454
00:28:20.550 --> 00:28:22.680
It's a legendary island.

455
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.060
Laugh Tale...

456
00:28:24.060 --> 00:28:26.890
So is that where the One Piece is?!

457
00:28:26.890 --> 00:28:29.940
Who knows. That's the most
prominent theory,

458
00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:32.650
but no one else has
been able to get there.

459
00:28:32.650 --> 00:28:34.280
Then...

460
00:28:34.280 --> 00:28:35.820
we'll be the first to prove it.

461
00:28:38.700 --> 00:28:41.410
Alright, I'm done!
You guys wanna get going?

462
00:28:41.410 --> 00:28:43.240
You ate the whole thing?!

463
00:28:43.240 --> 00:28:44.910
Whoa! Even the bones are gone.

464
00:28:44.910 --> 00:28:48.210
A log pose, huh? We'd better
take good care of this.

465
00:28:48.210 --> 00:28:50.420
This is the key to
the rest of our journey.

466
00:28:50.420 --> 00:28:52.170
You damn rubber man!

467
00:28:52.170 --> 00:28:54.800
I made Nami such 
a delicious meal and she...

468
00:28:55.590 --> 00:28:58.720
she didn't even have a bite!

469
00:29:13.610 --> 00:29:14.570
What was that for?

470
00:29:14.570 --> 00:29:16.990
Take that, you damn rubber man.

471
00:29:15.900 --> 00:29:16.990
Sanji...

472
00:29:16.990 --> 00:29:18.440
Yes, Nami!

473
00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:22.410
You two should go
cool your heads off!

474
00:29:26.790 --> 00:29:28.790
Hey, hold on a sec...

475
00:29:29.250 --> 00:29:32.540
Wasn't that thing
super-duper important?!

476
00:29:32.540 --> 00:29:35.040
Our precious log pose...

477
00:29:35.040 --> 00:29:37.380
Don't panic. You can have mine.

478
00:29:37.800 --> 00:29:40.300
Think of it as thanks
for helping Laboon.

479
00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:49.810
Man... I thought I was a goner. Huh?

480
00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:55.570
Here, take my hand, dear lady.

481
00:29:55.570 --> 00:29:56.610
Oh, thank you.

482
00:29:56.610 --> 00:29:57.820
Nice day, isn't it?

483
00:29:57.820 --> 00:29:58.610
Hey!

484
00:29:59.240 --> 00:30:00.530
We must ask you a favor.

485
00:30:04.160 --> 00:30:05.450
Whisky Peak?

486
00:30:05.780 --> 00:30:06.990
That's a weird name.

487
00:30:06.990 --> 00:30:08.080
What's that?

488
00:30:08.080 --> 00:30:10.830
That's where we live... um, sir.

489
00:30:10.830 --> 00:30:12.960
What happened to your ship?

490
00:30:12.960 --> 00:30:15.420
I'm afraid it was destroyed.

491
00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:20.130
That's a pretty big favor for someone
who just tried to kill the whale, Mr. 9.

492
00:30:20.550 --> 00:30:22.470
So who are you guys, anyway?

493
00:30:22.470 --> 00:30:24.180
I'm a king.

494
00:30:25.260 --> 00:30:26.220
Liar.

495
00:30:27.470 --> 00:30:29.220
We can't say!

496
00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:31.480
We just want to go back home.

497
00:30:31.480 --> 00:30:34.810
We don't like being
secretive either, but...

498
00:30:34.810 --> 00:30:37.230
...our company motto is "Mystery."

499
00:30:37.230 --> 00:30:39.650
We simply can't tell you
anything about us.

500
00:30:39.980 --> 00:30:43.360
Trusting your good
character, we beg of you!

501
00:30:43.360 --> 00:30:45.740
I assure you, we will return the favor.

502
00:30:45.740 --> 00:30:47.580
Don't do it.

503
00:30:47.580 --> 00:30:50.660
No matter what they say,
they're dishonest people.

504
00:30:51.080 --> 00:30:56.170
By the way, we broke the log pose.
Do you still want a ride?

505
00:30:56.500 --> 00:30:59.710
What?! You broke it?!
That was mine, you know!

506
00:30:59.710 --> 00:31:03.760
You dare act smug while we're being
humble?! You're all stuck here as well!

507
00:31:04.130 --> 00:31:05.550
Oh, I forgot to mention...

508
00:31:05.550 --> 00:31:08.720
We do have a spare,
courtesy of Mr. Crocus.

509
00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:11.720
We beg you people
of such character...

510
00:31:12.100 --> 00:31:14.690
Dammit! This minx is toying with us!

511
00:31:15.020 --> 00:31:16.520
Sure, you can ride with us.

512
00:31:17.940 --> 00:31:19.400
Whisky Peak, right?

513
00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:20.570
Let's go there.

514
00:31:20.570 --> 00:31:21.320
– What?
– Huh?

515
00:31:21.320 --> 00:31:25.530
Hey, are you sure we wanna go out of
our way to take these shady guys?

516
00:31:25.910 --> 00:31:26.950
What's the problem?

517
00:31:26.950 --> 00:31:28.990
Don't sweat the small stuff.

518
00:31:28.990 --> 00:31:33.960
Once you choose your route here,
you won't be able to change it.

519
00:31:33.960 --> 00:31:36.790
If we don't like it,
we'll just go around again.

520
00:31:37.330 --> 00:31:38.710
Is that so...?

521
00:31:39.250 --> 00:31:41.090
So, should we get going?

522
00:31:42.460 --> 00:31:45.550
Since I've made my promise
with the whale, let's sail out.

523
00:31:45.930 --> 00:31:48.300
Who in the world are you?

524
00:31:48.300 --> 00:31:49.260
Me?

525
00:31:49.260 --> 00:31:50.140
I'm...

526
00:31:50.560 --> 00:31:52.720
the man who's gonna be
King of the Pirates!

527
00:31:57.190 --> 00:31:58.770
What a foolish pirate...

528
00:32:01.650 --> 00:32:03.190
You should be good to go.

529
00:32:03.190 --> 00:32:05.240
The log must have
been stored by now.

530
00:32:05.860 --> 00:32:08.320
Is it pointing at the same
direction as the map?

531
00:32:08.320 --> 00:32:09.070
Yep.

532
00:32:09.780 --> 00:32:11.740
It's pointing at Whisky Peak.

533
00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:14.080
See ya, flower guy!

534
00:32:14.080 --> 00:32:15.660
Thanks for the log pose!

535
00:32:15.660 --> 00:32:17.580
Yeah. Have a safe trip!

536
00:32:17.580 --> 00:32:20.210
See ya, too, whale! I'm leaving now!

537
00:32:25.170 --> 00:32:27.130
Full speed ahead...

538
00:32:27.130 --> 00:32:29.510
to Whisky Peak!

539
00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:31.510
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

540
00:32:49.160 --> 00:32:54.040
Could they be the pirates we've been
waiting for all this time...?

541
00:32:54.040 --> 00:32:58.000
That man has a particularly
strange air about him...

542
00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:02.250
don't you think,

543
00:33:02.250 --> 00:33:03.960
Roger?
